Sure, here are some examples:

1. *Tiše* neću moći da spavam zbog buke. (*Tiše* - adverb, meaning "quieter") (I won't be able to sleep quieter because of the noise.)
2. Ti si *tiši* od svog brata. (*Tiši* - comparative form of adjective, meaning "quieter") (You are quieter than your brother.)
3. Molim vas, govorite *tiše*. (*Tiše* - adverb, meaning "quieter") (Please, speak quieter.)
4. Želim da *tiše* radiš, jer me smeta buka. (*Tiše* - adverb, meaning "more quietly") (I want you to work more quietly, because the noise bothers me.)
5. Oni su *tiši* kad su sami. (*Tiši* - comparative form of adjective, meaning "quieter") (They are quieter when they are alone.)
6. *Tišina* vlada u kući kad su svi otišli. (*Tišina* - noun, meaning "silence") (Silence reigns in the house when everyone has left.)
7. Vrata su *tiša* nakon što smo ih podmazali. (*Tiša* - comparative form of adjective, meaning "quieter") (The door is quieter after we lubricated it.)
8. Dan je bio *tiši* nego inače zbog kiše. (*Tiši* - comparative form of adjective, meaning "quieter") (The day was quieter than usual because of the rain.)
9. On govori *tiše* nego ja. (*Tiše* - adverb, meaning "more quietly") (He speaks more quietly than I do.)
10. *Tišina* je potrebna za dobar san. (*Tišina* - noun, meaning "silence") (Silence is necessary for a good sleep.)